{{term|international protectionrating |content={{vanchor|international protection (IP) rating|IP rating|IP Rating}} }}
{{term|ingress protection rating|multi=y}}
{{defn|content={{main|IP Code}}
A rating system that defines the protection of a product or enclosure against the ingress of solid objects and liquids. Consists of the letters IP followed by two digits and an optional letter. As defined in international standard IEC 60529, it classifies the degrees of protection provided against the intrusion of solid objects (including body parts like hands and fingers), dust, accidental contact, and water in electrical enclosures.}}

{{term|intrinsic safety barrier}}
{{defn|content=A network that is designed to limit the energy (voltage and current) available to the protected circuit in a hazardous (classified) location, under specified fault conditions.}}

{{term|intrinsic safety ground bus}}
{{defn|content=A grounding system with a dedicated conductor, which is separate from the power system so that ground currents will not normally flow, and reliably connected to a ground electrode in accordance with Article 200 of the NEC.}}

{{term|intrinsically safe circuit}}
{{defn|content=A circuit in which the ignition of a mixture of flammable or combustible material in air cannot be caused by a spark or thermal effect, under prescribed test conditions in its most easily ignitable concentration.}}

{{term|intrinsically safe system}}
{{defn|content=An assembly of interconnected intrinsically safe apparatus, associated apparatus and interconnecting cables in which the parts of the system, which may be used in hazardous (classified) locations, are intrinsically safe circuits; may include more than one intrinsically safe circuit.}}
{{glossary end}}

