{{update|date=November 2014}} {{Infobox pipeline | name = Pony Express Pipeline | type = [[Crude oil]] | photo = | caption = | map =http://www.tallgrassenergylp.com/Pipelines/Images/PXP_Crude_Project.pdf | country = United States | state = | province = | coordinates = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|type:landmark_region:XX|display=inline,title}} --> | lat = | long = | direction = | start = [[Guernsey, Wyoming]] | through = | finish = [[Cushing, Oklahoma]] | par = | owner = Tallgrass Energy Partners | partners = | operator = | technical_service_provider = | contractors = | construction = | expected = | est = | decom = | length_mi = 760 | discharge = | discharge_bbl_d = 0.23 | diameter_mm = | diameter_in = | compressor_stations_no =10 | compressor_stations = | pumping_stations_no = | pumping_stations = | website = [http://www.tallgrassenergy.com/Pipelines/PonyExpress/ Pipeline Website] }}
The '''Pony Express Pipeline''' ('''PXP''') is a {{convert|760|mi|adj=on}} pipeline connecting [[Guernsey, Wyoming]] with the oil hub of [[Cushing, Oklahoma]].
==Overiew== In 2013 agreement was reached to convert the [[natural gas]] pipeline to carry crude oil from the [[Bakken formation]] shale plays in [[North Dakota]] and [[Montana]]. It is supposed to connect with the planned [[Double H Pipeline]]. The project is being developed by Tallgrass Pony Express Pipeline, LLC ([[Tallgrass Energy Partners]]). Construction was completed in October 2014.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/kansascity/news/2014/10/09/tallgrass-energy-partners-pony-express-pipeline.html|title=Tallgrass completes 690-mile Pony Express pipeline project - Kansas City Business Journal|website=Kansas City Business Journal|access-date=2016-03-11}}</ref> The Pony Express Pipeline will have a capacity of {{convert|230,000|oilbbl/d}} and be expandable to more than {{convert|400,000|oilbbl/d}}.
